channel.description:
[u]Yell system for Project Insanity.[/u]

Requirements:  Pi.
Difficulty: 1/10
Tested ON: Project Insanity

Basically this uses the clanchat method and is perfect for those clients which doesnt have <img> - image code. Also if you are muted you cannot use yell channel.

[b]Example moderator yell.[/b]
1. Step - PlayerAssistant class:
[code]
	public void modYell(String Message) {
		for (int j = 0; j < Server.playerHandler.players.length; j++) {
			if (Server.playerHandler.players[j] != null) {
				Client c2 = (Client) Server.playerHandler.players[j];
				c2.sendClan(c.playerName, Message, "Moderator", c.playerRights);
			}
		}
	}[/code]

2. Step - Commands class:

[code]		if (playerCommand.startsWith("yell")) {
			String Message = playerCommand.substring(4).toLowerCase();
			if (Connection.isMuted(c)) {
				[color=pink]c.sendMessage("You cannot yell you are muted.");
			} else if (c.playerRights == 1) {
				c.getPA().modYell(Misc.optimizeText(Message));
			}
		}[/code]
Explainment:
sendClan - Sends a clanchat message.
c.playerName - The player name which will be displayed.
Message - The message which player writes through yell.
Moderator - Yell tag.
c.playerRights - Player rights, the icon which will be displayed.
Connection.isMuted - If connection is muted...
c.sendMessage - Sends a message in the chatbox. (For this shows the message that the player is muted and cannot use the yell channel.
c.playerRights - Defines the player rights
modYell - The voids name.
Misc.optimizeText(Message) - Sends the message what client typed.

Also if there will be some errors (lol) then post.
